# Configuring Google Cloud Credentials

To use Google Cloud Vision and Text-to-Speech APIs, you need to download your Google Cloud credentials file (usually named `google_cloud.json`).

1. Go to the [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/).
2. Navigate to your project and create a service account key with the necessary permissions.
3. Download the credentials file as `google_cloud.json`.
4. Place the `google_cloud.json` file here
